external_knowledge:
- 'Action' genre refers to movies that typically feature exciting and dynamic scenes, often with high energy and fast-paced action;
- 'More than 10 admirers' implies that the movie has received more than 10 individual ratings;
- 'Average rating' is calculated by summing all the ratings and dividing by the total number of ratings.

- "stars" refers to users who are part of a watchlist;
- "illuminated their watchlists" refers to users who have rated movies;
- "at least three movie ratings" means the users have rated at least 3 movies.

- "Unique contributors" refers to the number of distinct users who have rated or reviewed a movie;
- "Total ratings value" is the sum of all rating values for a movie;
- "Total review rating value" is the sum of all review ratings for a movie.

- "Sailed through the storm of user opinions" refers to movies that have received a significant number of ratings, specifically at least five;
- "Emerged with an average rating" means the average rating of the movie, calculated from the ratings given by users;
- "Cinematic treasures" refers to the movies and their respective franchises.

- 'Active reviewers' are users who have contributed both reviews and ratings;
- 'Total activity' is the sum of the number of reviews and ratings a user has made;
- 'Average rating on reviewed movies' is the mean rating of the movies that a user has reviewed.

- 'Highly rated' refers to movies with an average rating greater than 4.0;
- 'Substantial number of non-anonymous reviews' means more than 100 ratings;
- 'The Mummy Series' is a franchise of movies.

- 'Animation' refers to a specific genre of movies;
- 'Multiple reviews' means more than one review;
- 'Super admin' refers to an admin with elevated privileges.
